content:
Map each input required by your rating procedure must be mapped to an attribute in the product to be rated.

Map inputs to attributes associated with child specs first. Then associate those child specs with a root product spec. This lets all root products that use some of the same coverages, insured items, and insured parties use the same mapped rating inputs.

To map a rating input:

On the Product list page, find and open the child spec detail page you want to map ratings inputs to.
Select an attribute to map.
In the right panel, select Rating.
Under Rating Type, select Input.
Under Rating Input, enter the variable name from the rating procedure that maps to this attribute.
Click Update at the top of the right panel.

Verify and change rating input mappings as needed.
title: Mapping Rating Inputs in Insurance
